A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the House Study Committee on Improving Access to Internal Medicine in Rural
2 Areas; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, 75 percent of Georgia counties are considered rural; and
4 WHEREAS, rural Georgian communities often lack access to quality health care; and
5 WHEREAS, as of 2022, one in ten Georgians live in a county with no more than a single
6 physician; and
7 WHEREAS, recent studies have reported that approximately 40 counties, making up roughly
8 one-quarter of Georgia's total county count, have no internal medicine physician; and
9 WHEREAS, Georgia ranked fortieth among all states in the ratio of active patient care
10 physicians to the population, with one physician for every 480 people; and
11 WHEREAS, as of last year, 142 of Georgia's 159 counties are healthcare professional
12 shortage areas, meaning there are 3,500 or more patients for every one provider; and
