13 WHEREAS, rural communities within the state are challenged with recruiting and retaining
14 healthcare providers and staff; and
15 WHEREAS, transportation is not always accessible in rural areas of the state; and
16 WHEREAS, three out of four counties in Georgia are considered health transportation
17 shortage areas; and
18 WHEREAS, health transportation shortage areas experience increased levels of
19 transportation barriers to healthcare, such as public transportation availability and high
20 household poverty rates; and
21 WHEREAS, a study committee is needed to thoroughly evaluate the most prudent and
22 cost-effective ways to increase access to internal medicine in rural Georgian communities,
23 with particular focus on those rural communities experiencing health transportation
24 shortages.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES:
26 (1) Creation of House study committee. There is created the House Study Committee
27 on Improving Access to Internal Medicine in Rural Areas.
28 (2) Members and officers.
29 (A) The committee shall be composed of eight members.
30 (B) The Speaker of the House of Representatives shall appoint five members of the
31 House of Representatives.
32 (C) The Speaker shall also appoint an additional three nonlegislative members of the
33 committee who are licensed healthcare providers in this state and who are familiar with
34 the needs of rural Georgia.
